        "observed_type": "image_caption",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Figure 11-4. High-side Switching with an NPN BJT Driving a PNP BJT",
        "bbox": [
          0.14095238095238094,
          0.23358723249909322,
          0.7171428571428572,
          0.25244831338411317
        ],
        "order": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_2",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Low-side switching (Recipe 11.1) is the most common and simplest arrangement, and unless you have a good reason such as the need for one end of the load to be connected to ground, you should use low-side switching.",
        "bbox": [
          0.1419047619047619,
          0.27058396808124774,
          0.86,
          0.32789263692419296
        ],
        "order": 3
      }
    ]
  },
