        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "For a discussion of NPN and PNP bipolar transistors, see Recipe 5.1.",
        "bbox": [
          0.14285714285714285,
          0.3764961915125136,
          0.7133333333333334,
          0.39608269858541895
        ],
        "order": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_5",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "GPIO ports and their output logic are described in Recipe 10.7.",
        "bbox": [
          0.1419047619047619,
          0.4047878128400435,
          0.6695238095238095,
          0.4243743199129489
        ],
        "order": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_6",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "You willfind an example of switching with a transistor using an Arduino in Recipe 11.6 and for a Raspberry Pi in Recipe 11.7.",
        "bbox": [
          0.13904761904761906,
          0.43307943416757344,
          0.8590476190476191,
          0.47152702212549874
        ],
        "order": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_7",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "For switching using a MOSFET, see Recipe 11.3.",
        "bbox": [
          0.14095238095238094,
          0.4802321363801233,
          0.5438095238095239,
          0.4998186434530287
