  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0005",
    "kind": "section_text_panel",
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "primary_id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_9",
    "source": "header_anchor",
    "member_count": 2,
    "elements": [
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_9",
        "observed_type": "title",
        "canon_role": "section_header",
        "text": "Problem",
        "bbox": [
          0.14095238095238094,
          0.5622052956111716,
          0.23238095238095238,
          0.5861443598113892
        ],
        "order": 10
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_10",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "You want to allow a GPIO pin to control more power than it otherwise could, but a BJT isn't enough.",
        "bbox": [
          0.1419047619047619,
          0.5955749002538991,
          0.861904761904762,
          0.6340224882118245
        ],
        "order": 11
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0006",
    "kind": "section_text_panel",
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "primary_id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_11",
    "source": "header_anchor",
    "member_count": 4,
    "elements": [
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_11",
        "observed_type": "title",
        "canon_role": "section_header",
        "text": "Solution",
        "bbox": [
          0.14095238095238094,
          0.6499818643453029,
          0.23238095238095238,
          0.6746463547334058
        ],
        "order": 12
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_12",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "You can use a MOSFET as an electronic switch. Use the transistor in a common- source arrangement. Figure 11-5 shows the schematic for this circuit. Along with Recipe 11.1, you will find yourself using this circuit a lot.",
        "bbox": [
          0.1419047619047619,
          0.6833514689880305,
          0.86,
          0.7399347116430903
        ],
        "order": 13
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_13",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "This type of switching is called \"low-side\" switching because the transistor acts as a switch between the low voltage of GND and the load.",
        "bbox": [
          0.1419047619047619,
          0.7486398258977149,
          0.86,
          0.7870874138556402
        ],
        "order": 14
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_14",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "If the GPIO pin is high (3.3V or 5V) and exceeds the gate-threshold voltage of the MOSFET, the MOsFET will turn on, allowing current to flow from +V through the load to GND.",
        "bbox": [
          0.1419047619047619,
          0.7965179542981502,
          0.8590476190476191,
          0.8538266231410954
        ],
        "order": 15
      }
    ]
  }
]